      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 997.1 Carrera S, an analog benchmark featuring the M97 3.8L flat-six mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. This specimen is mechanically flawless, featuring a factory-spec PASM (Porsche Active Suspension Management) system and a documented IMS bearing retrofit for total peace of mind. The powerplant exhibits exceptional compression across all cylinders with zero bore scoring and a clean DME report showing no over-revs in higher ranges. Finished in its original paint with uniform depth readings, the chassis remains stiff and responsive, supported by fresh bushings and a limited-slip differential. This is a turn-key example for the discerning collector seeking peak hydraulic-steering feedback and naturally aspirated performance.",
